Description: Fix point cloud particle size in OpenGL Core Profile
 In OpenGL Core Profile, writing gl_PointSize in a vertex shader has no
 effect unless GL_PROGRAM_POINT_SIZE is explicitly enabled.  Without it,
 the rasteriser uses the API-level fixed point size (default 1.0), so all
 particles appear as single pixels regardless of the pointsize uniform.
 .
 In the original Compatibility Profile context (the GLX code did not
 request SDL_GL_CONTEXT_PROFILE_CORE), GL_VERTEX_PROGRAM_POINT_SIZE was
 often enabled by default by drivers, hiding the issue.  The SDL2 port
 requests Core Profile explicitly, making the enable mandatory.
